        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:43:11"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Those are only the first two paths. The wave can make repeated round trips inside the barrier, creating a whole geometric series of reflected amplitudes.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.13,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:43:11"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Their relative phases depend on the internal wave number q and barrier width L. One traversal adds phase q L; one round trip adds two q L.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.32,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:43:11"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "When q L equals an integer times pi, the barrier contains an integer number of half wavelengths. The returning reflected contributions cancel the immediate reflection.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "cancel"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
